  "text": "Malvastrum coromandelianum samples Y193 and Y194 with yellow vein symptoms were found to be infected with malvastrum yellow vein virus (MYVV) [CITATION_1] . Partial sequencing of virus clones showed the two samples also to be infected with a TYLCCNV-like virus (data not shown), so the complete TYLCCNV-like DNA sequences from Y193 and Y194 (isolates Y193 and Y194) were determined. The sequences of Y193 and Y194 consist of 2742 and 2749 nt, respectively. The coding strategy for Y193 and Y194 is typical of begomoviruses, with two genes in the virion sense and four in the complementary sense, separated by an intergenic region (IR). Efforts to detect a possible DNA B component in M. coromandelianum plants, using specific primers PCRc1 and PBL1v2040 (Rojas et al., 1993) , were unsuccessful.",
  "correct_citation": {
